  [MG005] No authentication configured for server 'vulnerable-server'
  Category: static | Confidence: high
  Server 'vulnerable-server' has no authentication configured (transport: stdio). Any local process can invoke any of its 6 tool(s) without credentials.
  Exploit: An attacker with local access gains direct access to server 'vulnerable-server' and invokes sensitive tools without authentication, potentially reading data, executing commands, or modifying state.
  Evidence: fixtures/vulnerable.tools.json > servers[vulnerable-server].auth — Authentication is set to 'none' or not configured
    Raw: {"type": "none"}
  Remediation: Configure authentication for server 'vulnerable-server'. For network-accessible servers, use OAuth or mutual TLS. For local servers, use API keys with per-client scoping. Avoid shared secrets.
  CWE: CWE-306, CWE-287 | OWASP: A07:2021 | MCP: MCP01:2025, MCP07:2025

── 🟡 MEDIUM (6) ──

  [MG002] Over-permissioned tool 'manage_users': description implies limited scope but capabilities are broad
  Category: semantic | Confidence: medium
  Tool 'manage_users' (server 'vulnerable-server') description uses limited-intent language (view, list) but its name/parameters contain broad-capability indicators (delete, update, create, manage). This mismatch may hide dangerous operations behind benign descriptions.
  Exploit: An LLM or user grants access to 'manage_users' based on its benign description (containing: view, list), without realizing it can also perform dangerous operations implied by: delete, update, create, manage. An attacker exploits this mismatch to escalate privileges through the tool.
  Evidence: fixtures/vulnerable.tools.json > servers[vulnerable-server] > tools[manage_users].description — Description implies limited scope with keywords: view, list
    Raw: View and list user records
  Evidence: fixtures/vulnerable.tools.json > servers[vulnerable-server] > tools[manage_users].name/parameters — Name/parameters imply broad capabilities: delete, update, create, manage
    Raw: manage_users
  Remediation: Update the description of tool 'manage_users' to accurately reflect all capabilities including: delete, update, create, manage. Alternatively, split the tool into separate read-only and write/execute tools.
  CWE: CWE-285 | OWASP: A01:2021 | MCP: MCP02:2025

